                                {\sqrt{Ï€} \over 3} \begin{bmatrix} 1 & 1 & 1 \\
                                \sqrt{6}/2 & 0 & -\sqrt{6}/2 \\
                                1/\sqrt{2} &-\sqrt{2} & 1/\sqrt{2}
                                \end{bmatrix}
\end{align*}
$$
We can use this to expand a polynomial, e.g. $x^2$:
$$
Q_3^w \begin{bmatrix}
x_1^2 \\
x_2^2 \\
x_3^2 
\end{bmatrix} = {\sqrt{Ï€} \over 3} 
\begin{bmatrix} 1 & 1 & 1 \\
\sqrt{6}/2 & 0 & -\sqrt{6}/2 \\
